documentation:
Lark parser for our custom DSL inside Prisma Schemas, e.g.

```prisma
/// @Python(name: foo)
model bar {
  // ...
}
```

Build the GraphQL query

Example query:

query {
  result: findUniqueUser
  (
    where: {
      id: "ckq23ky3003510r8zll5m2hma"
    }
  )
  {
    id
    name
    profile {
      id
      user_id
      bio
    }
  }
}

Rendered node examples:

query {
    <children>
}

or

mutation {
    <children>
}

Rendered node example:

(
    key1: "1"
    key2: "["John","123"]"
    key3: true
    key4: {
        data: true
    }
)

Rendered node example:

{
    key1: "a"
    key2: 3
    key3: [
        "name"
    ]
}

Represents field selections

Example no include:

{
    id
    name
}

Example include={'posts': True}

{
    id
    name
    posts {
        id
        title
    }
}

Example include={'posts': {'where': {'title': {'contains': 'Test'}}}}

{
    id
    name
    posts(
        where: {
            title: {
                contains: 'Test'
            }
        }
    )
    {
        id
        title
    }
}
